<p>With the <a href="https://mail.mozilla.org/pipermail/rust-dev/2012-December/002787.html">release of Rust 0.5</a>, I polished up a little analysis of issues using R and the <a href="http://developer.github.com/v3/issues/">github issue API</a>.</p>

<p>I initially downloaded the data with python script; I almost figured out how to do it with R before deciding that wasn&#39;t really the point of this exercise. So I polished up the python script a bit instead; see <a href="https://bitbucket.org/DanC/metamath-tools/src/03e4d9f145e327e06c79a59650d56621f554f057/rustrate.py">rustrate</a> if you&#39;re curious.</p>

<h2>JSON to Dataframe</h2>

<p>To convert the JSON data from the github API to an R dataframe:</p>

<pre><code class="r">issue.data &lt;- function(file) {
    require(&quot;rjson&quot;)
    issue.object.list &lt;- fromJSON(file = file)

    data.frame(number = field(issue.object.list, &quot;number&quot;), title = field(issue.object.list, 
        &quot;title&quot;), created_at = as.POSIXct(field(issue.object.list, &quot;created_at&quot;)), 
        closed_at = as.POSIXct(field(issue.object.list, &quot;closed_at&quot;)), stringsAsFactors = FALSE, 
        row.names = &quot;number&quot;)
}


field &lt;- function(l, n) {
    as.vector(sapply(l, function(i) {
        x &lt;- i[[n]]
        ifelse(is.null(x), NA, x)
    }))
}
</code></pre>

<h2>Plotting Issues Over Time</h2>

<p>To get a count of open issues vs. time and plot it:</p>

<pre><code class="r">open.at &lt;- function(d) {
    open &lt;- data.frame(sign = 1, t = d$created_at)
    close &lt;- data.frame(sign = -1, t = d$closed_at[!is.na(d$closed_at)])
    both &lt;- rbind(open, close)

    both &lt;- both[order(both$t), ]
    both$open &lt;- cumsum(both$sign)
    both
}


plot.issues &lt;- function(both, main, pch = 3, other = NULL, other.pch = NULL) {
    both$color = &quot;blue&quot;
    if (!is.null(other)) {
        other$color = &quot;green&quot;
        both &lt;- rbind(both, other)
    }
    with(both, plot(open ~ t, xaxt = &quot;n&quot;, col = both$color, pch = 20, new = new, 
        main = main, xlab = &quot;&quot;, ylab = &quot;issues&quot;))

    atx &lt;- seq(min(both$t), max(both$t), by = 7 * 24 * 60 * 60)
    axis(1, at = atx, labels = format(atx, &quot;%b\n%d&quot;), padj = 0.5)
}
</code></pre>
